The paper deals with the analysis of the asymptotic performance of a code construction over a binary erasure channel, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT). The code construction is deterministic and involves the use of graphs, which are also common in computer science (cs.CC, cs.DS). The paper also discusses the design of irregular codes, which is a topic in coding theory and optimization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses a convergence result for sparse inhomogeneous random graphs, which is a topic in network science (cs.NI).
